ce:section.ce:para:
The XRD patterns for N-doped C-dots prepared at 1:0.5, 1:1, and 1:2 ratios of PEI to CA precursors are given in Fig. S2 (a), (b), and (c), respectively. It obvious that a broad diffraction peak at about 2θ = 28° for each N-doped C-dots synthesized at 1:0.5, 1:1, and 1:2 ratios of PEI-CA precursors are assigned to the turbostratic carbon phase at (002) crystal planes [32]. Also, the broad diffraction peaks at about 2θ = 41° for all N-doped C-dots is attributed to the carbon phase at (100) crystal planes. Moreover, the crystallite size of prepared N-doped C-Dots were calculated by using well-known Scherrer equation, Eq. (2);
(2) τ = Kλ / βcosθ
where “τ” is the mean size of the ordered (crystalline) domains, “K” is a dimensionless shape factor, “λ” is the X-ray wavelength, β is the line broadening at half the maximum intensity, θ is the Bragg angle [25].
